body:
A streaming data source generates a document for each order made with
an e-commerce platform. The documents take the following form:

```json
{
  orderId: 1,
  productId: "A",
  qty: 2
}
```

An Atlas database contains a `products` collection with
documents of the following form:

```json
[
  {_id: "A", name: "Laptop", category: "tech"},
  {_id: "B", name: "Shirt", category: "clothing"}
]
```

The following aggregation has six stages:

- The [$source](pipe.$source) stage ingests order documents from the
  e-commerce platform, exposing each record as it is ingeste to the
  subsequent aggregation stages.

- The [$lookup](atlas-sp-agg-lookup) stage joins the incoming
  order documents to a `products` collection in the `shop`
  database on the `_id` field. The resulting array field is called
  `product`.

- The [$unwind](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/unwind) stage turns the single-element array value
  of `product` into a document.

- The [$setStreamMeta](pipe.$setStreamMeta) stage sets a metadata field called
  `stream.coll` equal to the value of `product.category`.

- The [$unset](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/unset) stage removes the `product` field,
  returning the source document to its original form.

- The [$merge](atlas-sp-agg-merge) stage merges the document into a
  collection dynamically determined by the value of `stream.coll`.

```json
{
  $source: {
    documents: [
      {
        orderId: 1,
        productId: "A",
        qty: 2
      },
      {
        orderId: 2,
        productId: "B",
        qty: 1
      },
      {
        orderId: 3,
        productId: "A",
        qty: 5
      }
    ]
  }
},
{
  $lookup: {
    from: {
      connectionName: "atlas",
      db: "shop",
      coll: "products"
    },
    localField: "productId",
    foreignField: "_id",
    as: "product"
  }
},
{
  $unwind: "$product"
},
{
  $setStreamMeta: {
    "stream.coll": "$product.category"
  }
},
{
  $unset: [
    "product"
  ]
},
{
  $merge: {
    into: {
      connectionName: "atlas",
      db: "shop",
      coll: {
        $meta: "stream.coll"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

